article.headline: Montana St. 31, Sacramento St. 20
article.story: SACRAMENTO, Calif. -- Montana State quarterback Cody Kempt passed for 169 yards and two touchdowns in a 31-20 victory over Sacramento State on Saturday. Running back Demetrius Crawford ran for 112 yards and one touchdown for the Montana State Bobcats (4-4, 2-2 Big Sky), who have beaten Sacramento State in seven of their last eight meetings. Bryan Hilliard ran for 96 yards and two touchdowns for the Sacramento State Hornets (3-5, 1-4 Big Sky), who have lost their last three games. Crawford's 9-yard touchdown run and freshman receiver DeSean Thomas' 58-yard catch set up a field goal to give the Bobcats a 10-0 lead in the first quarter. The Bobcats finished the first-half with a 17-0 shutout when Brandon Bostick caught a 5-yard TD from Kempt with six minutes left in the second quarter. Sac State linebacker Cyrus Mulitalo returned an interception 53 yards to set up a 1-yard score on fourth down by Hilliard in the third quarter. Bobcats' safety Kevin Retoriano scored on a blocked punt in the third quarter and Derek Green caught an 18-yard TD in the middle of fourth quarter to give Montana State a 31-7 lead.
